@startuml
title Binary Field - Class View

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

namespace spk {
	class BinaryField {
		- shared_ptr<Layout> _layout
		- size_t _sectionID
		+ BinaryField(data, size)
		+ addValue(name, offset, size) : BinaryField
		+ addObject(name, offset, size) : BinaryField
		+ addArray(name, offset, count, elementSize) : BinaryField
		+ operator[](name) : BinaryField
		+ operator[](index) : BinaryField
		+ isValid() : bool
		+ name() : string_view
		+ size() : size_t
		+ offset() : size_t
		+ count() : size_t
		+ elementSize() : size_t
		+ data() : uint8_t*
		+ operator=<TValueType>(value) : BinaryField&
		+ operator=<TValueType, N>(array) : BinaryField&
		+ set<TValueType>(value) : BinaryField&
		+ as<TValueType>() : TValueType
		+ bytes() : span<uint8_t>
	}

	class "BinaryField::Section" as Section {
		- string name
		- Kind kind
		- size_t size
		- size_t offset
		- size_t absoluteOffset
		- size_t elementSize
		- size_t count
		- size_t parent
		- vector<size_t> children
	}

	class "BinaryField::Layout" as Layout {
		- uint8_t* data
		- vector<Section> sections
	}
}

spk.BinaryField *-- Layout : shared layout
Layout *-- Section

note right of spk.BinaryField
BinaryField is a non-owning byte view.
Sections are explicit byte ranges inside their parent.
Assignment requires exact byte-size matches.
Arrays create one value child section per index.
Named children can be added only to object sections.
end note

@enduml
